I"T<h1>Revenue Measures Overview</h1>
<p>This document holds all the DAX revenue measures used in the creation of the dashboards in my EDA.</p>
<p><b>Note:</b> The measure <code>recalculate_total_order_value</code> was renamed to <code>product_value</code>. It is created by adding <code>price</code> and <code>freight_value</code> together.</p>

<div class="hr-wrapper">
  <hr class="title" />
</div>

<h2>Revenue Measures</h2>

<details class="section-details">
  <summary><b>1. Total Product Revenue</b></summary>
  <p><b>Description:</b> Calculates the total revenue generated by summing up the product values across all rows in the <code>Order_Items_Final</code> table. Returns <code>0</code> if no product values are found.</p>
  <details class="code-details">
    <summary>ðŸ“‚ <b>DAX Measure</b></summary>
    <pre><code class="language-dax">
<!-- prettier ignore -->
Total Product Revenue = 
IF(
    ISBLANK(SUM(Order_Items_Final[product_value])),
    0,
    SUM(Order_Items_Final[product_value])
)
    </code></pre>
  </details>
</details>

<div class="hr-wrapper">
  <hr />
</div>

<details class="section-details">
  <summary><b>2. Average Product Revenue</b></summary>
  <p><b>Description:</b> Calculates the average revenue per product by dividing the total product value by the total number of rows in the <code>Order_Items_Final</code> table. Returns <code>0</code> if no rows exist.</p>
  <details class="code-details">
    <summary>ðŸ“‚ <b>DAX Measure</b></summary>
    <pre><code class="language-dax">
<!-- prettier ignore -->
Average Product Revenue = 
DIVIDE(
    SUM('Order_Items_Final'[product_value]),
    COUNTROWS('Order_Items_Final'),
    0
)
    </code></pre>
  </details>
</details>

<div class="hr-wrapper">
  <hr />
</div>

<details class="section-details">
  <summary><b>3. Median Revenue</b></summary>
  <p><b>Description:</b> Calculates the median product value for all rows in the <code>Order_Items_Final</code> table using <code>MEDIANX</code>.</p>
  <details class="code-details">
    <summary>ðŸ“‚ <b>DAX Measure</b></summary>
    <pre><code class="language-dax">
<!-- prettier ignore -->
Median Revenue = 
MEDIANX(
    'Order_Items_Final',
    'Order_Items_Final'[product_value]
)
    </code></pre>
  </details>
</details>

<div class="hr-wrapper">
  <hr />
</div>

<details class="section-details">
  <summary><b>4. Weighted Average Revenue</b></summary>
  <p><b>Description:</b> Calculates the weighted average revenue by taking into account the quantity sold for each product. The total revenue is calculated as the product of <code>product_value</code> and <code>product_quantity</code>, divided by the total quantity.</p>
  <details class="code-details">
    <summary>ðŸ“‚ <b>DAX Measure</b></summary>
    <pre><code class="language-dax">
<!-- prettier ignore -->
Weighted Average Revenue = 
DIVIDE(
    SUMX(
        'Order_Items_Final',
        'Order_Items_Final'[product_value] * 'Order_Items_Final'[product_quantity]
    ),
    SUM('Order_Items_Final'[product_quantity]),
    0
)
    </code></pre>
  </details>
</details>

<div class="hr-wrapper">
  <hr />
</div>

<h2>Revenue Percentages</h2>

<details class="section-details">
  <summary><b>1. Revenue Percentage</b></summary>
  <p><b>Description:</b> Calculates the percentage of revenue for the current context compared to the total revenue across all rows in the <code>Order_Items_Final</code> table.</p>
  <details class="code-details">
    <summary>ðŸ“‚ <b>DAX Measure</b></summary>
    <pre><code class="language-dax">
<!-- prettier ignore -->
Revenue Percentage = 
DIVIDE(
    [Total Product Revenue],
    CALCULATE(
        [Total Product Revenue],
        ALL(Order_Items_Final)
    ),
    0
)
    </code></pre>
  </details>
</details>

<div class="hr-wrapper">
  <hr />
</div>

<details class="section-details">
  <summary><b>2. Revenue Percentage by Category</b></summary>
  <p><b>Description:</b> Calculates the revenue percentage for each product category by dividing the revenue for the current category by the total revenue across all categories.</p>
  <details class="code-details">
    <summary>ðŸ“‚ <b>DAX Measure</b></summary>
    <pre><code class="language-dax">
<!-- prettier ignore -->
Revenue Percentage by Category = 
DIVIDE(
    [Total Product Revenue],
    CALCULATE(
        [Total Product Revenue],
        REMOVEFILTERS('Order_Items_Final'),
        VALUES('Order_Items_Final'[Product Category])
    ),
    0
)
    </code></pre>
  </details>
</details>

<div class="hr-wrapper">
  <hr />
</div>

<details class="section-details">
  <summary><b>3. Percentage of Revenue per Product Category</b></summary>
  <p><b>Description:</b> Calculates the percentage of total revenue for each product category using <code>Category Rankings</code>.</p>
  <details class="code-details">
    <summary>ðŸ“‚ <b>DAX Measure</b></summary>
    <pre><code class="language-dax">
<!-- prettier ignore -->
Percentage of Revenue per Product Category = 
DIVIDE(
    [Total Product Revenue],
    CALCULATE(
        [Total Product Revenue],
        REMOVEFILTERS('Order_Items_Final'),
        VALUES('Category Rankings'[product_category])
    ),
    0
)
    </code></pre>
  </details>
</details>

<div class="hr-wrapper">
  <hr />
</div>

<details class="section-details">
  <summary><b>4. Percentage of Revenue per Bin Range</b></summary>
  <p><b>Description:</b> Calculates the percentage of total revenue for each product value bin, allowing analysis of revenue distribution across predefined ranges.</p>
  <details class="code-details">
    <summary>ðŸ“‚ <b>DAX Measure</b></summary>
    <pre><code class="language-dax">
<!-- prettier ignore -->
Percentage of Revenue per Bin Range = 
DIVIDE(
    [Total Product Revenue],
    CALCULATE(
        [Total Product Revenue],
        REMOVEFILTERS('Order_Items_Final'),
        VALUES('Order_Items_Final'[Product Value Bins])
    ),
    0
)
    </code></pre>
  </details>
</details>

<div class="hr-wrapper">
  <hr />
</div>
